This paper deals with the application of polar codes in deletion channels, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also proposes a list decoding algorithm with a cyclic redundancy check, which is a technique used in cryptography (cs.CR). The optimization of the amount of redundancy added is a problem related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The numerical simulations involve statistical analysis and machine learning (cs.SI). Finally, the use of error-correcting codes is a topic related to network information theory (cs.NI).
